      <h2>3. Data Flow</h2>
      <p></p>

      <ul>
        <li>All product data is stored as JSON inside <code>/data/</code></li>
        <li>The API serves product categories through Express routes</li>
        <li>
          Each frontend page fetches its category using <code>fetch()</code>
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Example API fetch</h3>
      <pre>
fetch("/api/products/men")
  .then(res => res.json())
  .then(data => renderProducts(data));
    </pre
      >

      <hr />
      <h3>Search System</h3>
      <p>
        The search is powered by Fuse.js which provides fuzzy search with high
        accuracy.
      </p>
      <ul><li>Search filtering is done using Fuse.js for better accuracy</li></ul>
      <pre>
const fuse = new Fuse(results, {
    keys: ["description", "site"],
    threshold: 0.3,
    });
    results = fuse.search(word).map((r) => r.item);
    });</pre>
